<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Valhalla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The mighty <b>Valhalla</b> is <a href="/index.php/Non-Vanilla_Ships" title="Non-Vanilla Ships" class="mw-redirect">not available in a vanilla game</a>, but present in the game files.  This behemoth is canonically the flagship of the <a href="/index.php/ATF" title="ATF">ATF</a>, boasting large weapon arrays, spacious hangars and massive shields. It is also one of the largest craft in the game, being too wide to fit through gates. It is obviously unfinished, as there are also some turret placement and targeting bugs in its design. Its hangar can accommodate <a href="/index.php/M6" title="M6">M6</a> class ships, a trait shared only by the <a href="/index.php/Aran" title="Aran">Aran</a> and <a href="/index.php/Ozias" title="Ozias">Ozias</a>.
</p><p>In the literature, the Valhalla is classified as an <a href="/index.php/M0" title="M0">M0 Battleship</a>, but as there is no actual M0 classification in <i><a href="/index.php/X3:_Terran_Conflict" title="X3: Terran Conflict">X3: Terran Conflict</a></i>, it appears in-game as an <a href="/index.php/M2" title="M2">M2 Destroyer</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Valhalla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
